entry.def: A shopping precinct is an area in the centre of a town in which cars are not allowed.

example.ex: The Centre was a pedestrian precinct with a bandstand in the middle.
example.tran: 该中心是步行商业区，正中央有一个室外音乐演奏台。

entry.def: A precinct is a part of a city which has its own police force and fire service.

example.ex: The shooting occurred in the 34th Precinct.
example.tran: 枪击事件发生在第34警区。

entry.def: The precincts of an institution are its buildings and land.
